    • Method Detail

      • getEffectiveThrottleConstraint

        ThrottleConstraint getEffectiveThrottleConstraint()
        Returns the effective throttle constraint for this Method or null if this Method is not throttled.

        If this Method is part of a Plan, the Traffic Manager throttles each Application's requests for this method according to this throttle constraint.

        Returns:
        effective throttle constraint for this Method

      • getEffectiveRateConstraint

        RateConstraint getEffectiveRateConstraint()
        Returns the effective rate constraint for this Method or null if this Method is not rate constrained.

        If this Method is part of a @Plan, the Traffic Manager limits each Application's requests for this method according to this rate constraint.

        In the absence of a @Plan, the Traffic Manager may limit access to this Method across the entire Service if a rate constraint for this Method is configured on the @Endpoint.

        Returns:
        effective rate constraint for this Method

      • getKeyThrottleConstraint

        ThrottleConstraint getKeyThrottleConstraint()

        Key-specific throttle constraint for this Method or null if none
